     xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/">
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="https://purl.org/eudpp/MAT">
        <dcterms:contributor xml:lang="en">Riina Maigre</dcterms:contributor>
        <dcterms:created xml:lang="en">2026-04-10</dcterms:created>
        <dcterms:creator xml:lang="en">Tarmo Robal</dcterms:creator>
        <dcterms:description xml:lang="en">MODULE: MATERIAL
Material module of the  EU DPP core ontology proposal of the CIRPASS-2 European project.

DEPENDENCIES:  This module has dependencies to the following EU DPP Core Ontology (CO) modules: CON, P_DPP, SOC.  

Under the ESPR, products must disclose what materials they contain, where those materials come from, whether they include substances of concern, and how those materials support durability, repairability, recyclability, and circularity.
The main requiremetns regarding materials are given in ESPR Annex I. 


--
THIS DOCUMENT IS PROVIDED WITH NO WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER. 
All liability for any damages arising from use or misuse of this vocabulary is with the user.</dcterms:description>
        <dcterms:issued xml:lang="en">2026-04-28</dcterms:issued>
        <dcterms:licence rdf:resource="https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0"/>
        <dcterms:licence xml:lang="en">This ontology is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. 
In case of dispute over Apache 2.0 applicability, or in case considering the ontology as a document, this ontology document is to be considered licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0).</dcterms:licence>
        <dcterms:title xml:lang="en">The Materials (MAT) module of the EU DPP core ontology proposed by the CIRPASS-2 European project.</dcterms:title>
        <vann1:preferredNamespacePrefix>mat</vann1:preferredNamespacePrefix>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">First iteration of the Material module of the EU DPP core ontology proposal of the CIRPASS-2 European project.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">EU DPP MAT</rdfs:label>
        <owl:versionInfo>1.0.1</owl:versionInfo>
    </owl:Ontology>
    


